investigation.title: Salivary microbiome sequencing of astronauts
investigation.description: This study's goal was to examine if any salivary microbiome changes were observed in astronauts as a result of spaceflight. In addition, this study looked for any microbiome signature that may be associated with viral reactivation in humans

project.funding: Part of the research described in this publication was carried out at the Jet Propulsion Laboratory, California Institute of Technology, under a contract with NASA. We would like to thank all the astronauts who participated in this study which is funded by the NASA Human Research Program SMO-015 (CS) and NNX12AB02G (HL). This research was also funded by a 2012 Space Biology NNH12ZTT001N grant no. 19-12829-26 under Task Order NNN13D111T award to KV. This grant and NASA Post-doctoral Program sponsored by Space Biology are funded fellowship for CU. © 2019 California Institute of Technology. Government sponsorship acknowledged.
